final_hyps.green: The green object is the Goal that the agent must reach.
final_hyps.brown: Brown objects are False Walls. The agent can move through False Walls.
final_hyps.yellow: The yellow object is a Key. The agent can pick up the Key by moving into its space. While holding the Key, the agent is colored purple.
final_hyps.cyan: The cyan object is a KeyDoor. When the agent moves onto this object, the KeyDoor opens and the Key is destroyed. The agent cannot move through the KeyDoor while it is closed.

solve_plan: First determine that the green object is the Goal object. Because the cyan object is a KeyDoor, and the yellow object is a Key, the agent must first pick up the Key by moving to the yellow object at (13, 8) on the same horizontal axis (y=8). Next, move the agent to reach the Key at x=13 by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is at x=5, it must move RIGHT 13 - 5 = 8 times. Then, hold the Key and move to the KeyDoor at (18, 8) on the same horizontal axis (y=8). Next, move the agent to reach the KeyDoor at x=18 by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is already holding the Key and has moved past the yellow object, it must move RIGHT 18 - 13 = 5 times more. Then, because the agent is holding the Key and standing on the KeyDoor, the door opens, and the Key is destroyed. Finally, move the agent to reach the goal (x=19) by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is at x=18, it must move RIGHT 1 time.
